<p>One notable drawback is the transaction fees. Although these fees are standard in the industry, they can be a concern for businesses with tight profit margins. The costs associated with each transaction can add up, potentially impacting your overall profitability.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Additionally, some users might require technical assistance to resolve specific issues or fully customize the payment experience. While the integration process is generally straightforward, certain aspects might necessitate expert help, particularly if you want to tailor the payment gateway to meet unique business needs. This need for occasional technical support can be a drawback, especially for businesses that lack in-house technical expertise.</p>
